 Syntax:  .set <option> <setting>

Results:  This command allows a user to set various user attributes
          that can control the way the terminal functions or things
          that you wish to have available for others to see

To get a list of keywords/options, type:  .set
To see your settings now,          type:  .set show

Help on each keyword/option is in their own separate helpfile, since
there are too many options for one file.
 The format is: .h set_<option>

For example, help on setting your email address with the "email" option is
under ".h set_email"
